metadata.title: Which Countries Invest The Most In Education?
metadata.description: Expenditure on education as a % of total public expenditure in selected countries*
metadata.main_insight: New Zealand and Mexico invest the most in education as a percentage of their total public expenditure, at 21.6% and 20.5% respectively. Italy invests the least among the listed countries, at 8.6%.
